                <a href="category-2.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Phase 2: Workflow Automation</a>
            </p>
            <main>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">How to Automate QBR (Quarterly Business Review) Creation</h1>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>The Problem</th><th>The AI Solution</th></tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Manually pulling data from Tableau and Sheets to build QBR slides is a high-effort, manual task that takes hours.</td>
                        <td>Use Gemini in Google Docs to summarize raw data and extract insights. Then, use Gemini in Google Slides to automatically generate the presentation.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <div class="tag-container">
                    <span class="tag tag-indigo"><strong>Primary Roles:</strong> Account Managers, Account Directors</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-indigo"><strong>Tools:</strong> Gemini in Slides, Gemini in Docs</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-indigo"><strong>Difficulty / Phase:</strong> Phase 2: Workflow Automation</span>
                </div>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4 solution-h2">Step-by-Step Training Workflow</h2>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 1: Create Your "QBR Data Hub"</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Create a new Google Doc named <strong>"[Merchant Name] QBR Data - [Quarter]"</strong>. Copy and paste all your raw exported data (tables, charts, notes) into this single doc.</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 2: Use Gemini in Docs to Find the Story</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">In your Google Doc, open the <strong>Gemini Sidebar</strong> (✨ icon) and give it this prompt:</p>
                <pre><code>Act as a senior Account Director. Based *only* on the data in this document:
1.  Write a 3-paragraph executive summary for the "Key Takeaways" slide.
2.  Identify the 3 biggest "Performance Wins" (with data points).
3.  Identify 2 "Risks or Opportunities" (with data points).
4.  Suggest one "Data-Backed Recommendation" for next quarter.
Format the output clearly with headings.</code></pre>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 3: Generate the Slide Deck Automatically</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Open a new, blank Google Slides presentation. Open the <strong>Gemini Sidebar</strong> (✨ icon) and use an "@" prompt to reference your doc.</p>
                <pre><code>Create a 7-slide QBR presentation for [Merchant Name] based on my Google Doc named "@[Merchant Name] QBR Data - [Quarter]".

* Slide 1: Title slide
* Slide 2: The Executive Summary
* Slide 3: Performance Win 1
* ...etc.
* Slide 7: Recommendations & Next Steps</code></pre>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Pro-Tip: Use NotebookLM for Deeper Insights</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">For Tier A merchants, create a <strong>NotebookLM</strong> project. Upload <code>Past QBRs</code>, <code>Current IOs</code>, and your new <code>QBR Data Hub</code> doc. Then ask deeper questions.</p>
                <pre><code>Comparing the current data doc to the QBR from last quarter, what is the biggest change in performance?</code></pre>
            </main>
